<p data-start="319" data-end="378">
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. starch</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: starch</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn D, câu cuối: “The process for making Nature Works PLA begins when a renewable resource such as corn is milled, separating <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">starch</strong> from the raw material.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Quy trình bắt đầu bằng việc xay nghiền ngô (milling corn), từ đó tách được tinh bột (<strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">starch</strong>) ra khỏi nguyên liệu thô.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. fermentation</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: fermentation</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn E, câu 1: “Cargill Dow turns the unrefined dextrose into lactic acid using a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">fermentation</strong> process similar to that used by beer and wine producers.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Sau khi có đường dextrose thô (unrefined dextrose), quy trình sử dụng bước lên men (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">fermentation</strong>) để chuyển hóa nó thành axit lactic.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. condensation</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: condensation</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn E, câu 3: “Through a special <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">condensation</strong> process, a lactide is formed.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Để tạo ra lactide từ axit lactic, quy trình cần trải qua một bước đặc biệt gọi là sự ngưng tụ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">condensation</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. polymer</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: polymer</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn E, câu 4: “This lactide is purified through vacuum distillation and becomes a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">polymer</strong> (the base for Nature Works PLA)…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Tại bước chưng cất chân không (vacuum distillation), lactide được tinh chế và trở thành một polyme (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">polymer</strong>), đây chính là nền tảng để tạo ra sản phẩm Nature Works PLA cuối cùng.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('60072d43-f0b8-46cc-a7a7-77a18f53b7f9', '7ff11e44-f44a-4cef-a7fa-1b8af337f088', 'fillup', 'Questions 37–39', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>The use of fire</strong></p>
<p>Neanderthalers could not have survived without fire because the conditions they lived in were {sub-arctic} Most evidence of purpose-built fires takes the form of ash piles, features of which suggest that the fires lasted a {short} time. It is hard to be certain about the size and structure of the fires, though they were certainly needed to protect the occupants from dangerous {animals} among other things.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>37. Neanderthalers could not have survived without fire because the conditions they lived in were sub-arctic…</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>sub-arctic</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “…survival in the <strong>sub-arctic conditions</strong> faced by the Neanderthalers is inconceivable without control of fire.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>38. …features of which suggest that the fires lasted a short time.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>short</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “Judging from the shallow penetration of heat effects under the ash, this fire was only of a <strong>short duration</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>39. …to protect the occupants from dangerous animals among other things.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>animals</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “Fire gave warmth, light, heat for cooking and <strong>defence against predatory animals</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('19e60646-f59c-48c7-a838-a5ce2535e001', '4e920fd6-4b7a-49b8-ad56-eae88315dd93', 'matching', 'Questions 27-30', '', '<p>How will Kathy benefit from doing each of the following activities?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>answers from the box and write the correct letter,A-F</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Activities</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>going to Mechanical Engineers'' Society meetings {way to make useful contacts}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>visiting different workplaces {effective way of keeping up-to-date}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>getting some work experience abroad {broadens practical experience of the field}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>attending an international conference {chance to publicise own work}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "broadens practical experience of the field"}, {"optionText": "chance to publicise own work"}, {"optionText": "effective way of keeping up-to-date"}, {"optionText": "looks good on a CV"}, {"optionText": "provides useful access to resources"}, {"optionText": "way to make useful contacts"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cf467cfb-9018-4595-96d0-17a6cfd6c6e0', 'a1014b92-453c-4cbd-888d-a6612e8c6c98', 'radio', 'Questions 27–31', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mahy explores the traditional themes of New Zealand literature."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mahy’s children’s books have been more popular than her teenage books."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mahy and Knox have sometimes criticised each other’s work."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mahy is welcoming to interviewers."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mahy is at ease speaking about her experiences."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong class=\"\">27. Mahy explores the traditional themes of New Zealand literature.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: NO</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 1) “In our </span><strong class=\"\">solidly realist tradition</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> the linguistic fireworks of Mahy’s children’s fiction and the explorations of human behaviour in her supernatural teenage fiction </span><strong class=\"\">stand gloriously alone</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Truyền thống văn học New Zealand là hiện thực (</span><em class=\"\">realist tradition</em><span class=\"\">),</span><span class=\"\"> nhưng tác phẩm của Mahy lại </span><strong class=\"\">đứng một mình</strong><span class=\"\"> (</span><em class=\"\">stand gloriously alone</em><span class=\"\">) và đi vào </span><strong class=\"\">lãnh thổ giàu trí tưởng tượng</strong><span class=\"\"> (</span><em class=\"\">imaginative territory</em><span class=\"\">),</span><span class=\"\"> tức là bà </span><strong class=\"\">không</strong><span class=\"\"> khám phá các chủ đề truyền thống.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">28. Mahy’s children’s books have been more popular than her teenage books.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Văn bản chỉ nói chung về sự độc đáo của cả hai thể loại (children’s fiction và supernatural teenage fiction) và mức độ nổi tiếng của một số tác phẩm trẻ em (</span><em class=\"\">Bubble Trouble</em><span class=\"\">,</span> <em class=\"\">The Great White Man-Eating Shark</em><span class=\"\">).</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong> <strong class=\"\">Không có thông tin</strong><span class=\"\"> so sánh trực tiếp mức độ phổ biến giữa sách thiếu nhi và sách tuổi teen của bà.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">29. Mahy and Knox have sometimes criticised each other’s work.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 1) “Mahy’s clearest heir,</span><span class=\"\"> I have always thought,</span><span class=\"\"> is Elizabeth Knox…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả chỉ so sánh Mahy với Elizabeth Knox và coi Knox là người thừa kế rõ ràng nhất của bà,</span> <strong class=\"\">không đề cập</strong><span class=\"\"> đến việc họ có phê bình công việc của nhau hay không.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">30. Mahy is welcoming to interviewers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: YES</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 1) “</span><strong class=\"\">As with all journalists, she is generous to a fault with her time and attention</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Cụm từ “generous to a fault” (rộng lượng quá mức cần thiết) cho thấy bà rất niềm nở với các nhà báo.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">31. Mahy is at ease speaking about her experiences.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: NO</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 1) “…</span><span class=\"\">as always—despite her careful consideration of questions and thoughtful answers—</span><strong class=\"\">I’m reminded she isn’t truly comfortable making herself or her life the heart of any conversation</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả nhận thấy bà </span><strong class=\"\">không thực sự thoải mái</strong><span class=\"\"> khi nói về bản thân hoặc cuộc đời mình.</span></li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('00ee9730-b250-4739-9473-9d1e41c89a51', '6c0a9a17-d8b7-4e0d-b5c1-f1a2893290d7', 'radio', 'Questions 11-15', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, A,B or C.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. preparing their fields for planting."}, {"option_text": "B. harvesting their organic crops."}, {"option_text": "C. constructing their farm buildings."}], "question": "Stephen says the founders of extrahands.com originally needed help in"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. update your form on the website every year."}, {"option_text": "B. pay a subscription of $25 every year."}, {"option_text": "C. use the scheme as a host or volunteer every year."}], "question": "To remain an active member of extrahands.com, you must"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. the type of work available."}, {"option_text": "B. the geographical location."}, {"option_text": "C. the length of time required."}], "question": "Most extrahands.com volunteers search for jobs on the website according to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. confirm details of the arrangement in writing."}, {"option_text": "B. draw up a formal written contract."}, {"option_text": "C. meet each other before setting on terms."}], "question": "Stephen recommends that the host and volunteer should"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. for checking each new member online."}, {"option_text": "B. for allowing online feedback."}, {"option_text": "C. for inspecting work and accommodation."}], "question": "To deal with members''problems,extrahands.com have a system"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 2: EXTRA HANDS ORGANIZATION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Presenter:</strong> Steven Jennings has been involved with an intriguing organization called Extra hands.com. I''ll let him explain. </p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-146\" data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Steven:</strong>Thanks. Yes, Extra hands.com was started 15 years ago by two New Zealanders who''d bought an old farm building and some land. They wanted to go organic, but they realized they''d need help <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"187\">(Q11) <span class=\"citation-2068 citation-2069 citation-2070\">clearing the fields for cultivation</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2068 citation-2069 citation-2070 citation-end-2070\">, and they just didn''t have the money to pay for it. But they knew lots of people wanted to visit New Zealand, so they set up a website and advertised for volunteers to come and help on the farm there. Anyway, th<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2068 citation-2069 citation-end-2069\">ey got lots of volunteers and they got their farm going, and extra hands.com was born.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2068 citation-end-2068\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-147\" data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-2066 citation-2067 citation-end-2067\">Today the organization matches pe<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2066 citation-end-2066\">ople who need help with people who are willing to work as a way of seeing the world. You can either be a host if you need assistance or<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"5\"><!----></sup></span> a volunteer if you''re offering to work. In either case, to become a member, you just fill out a form on the Extra hands.com website and pay the 25 dollar subscription. You only have to do that once, but for your membership to stay active <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"407\">(Q12) <span class=\"citation-2064 citation-2065\">every 12 months you have to go back to the website and check the details on your form there</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2064 citation-2065 citation-end-2065\">, adding information about any help you requested or work you did over that period.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"6\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2064 citation-end-2064\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"7\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-148\" data-path-to-node=\"7\"><span class=\"citation-2062 citation-2063 citation-end-2063\">So how does it work? Well, if a host has some work that needs to be done, he or she goes t<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"8\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2062 citation-end-2062\">o the Ex<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"9\"><!----></sup></span>tra hands.com website and posts a description of the work. So the way most volunteers access these details on the website is by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"226\">(Q13) <span class=\"citation-2058 citation-2059 citation-2060 citation-2061\">specifying the country or region they''re interested in working in</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2058 citation-2059 citation-2060 citation-2061 citation-end-2061\">. But a few search according to how long they want to work for. Not many people have strong feelings about what sort of work they want to do<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"10\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2058 citation-2059 citation-2060 citation-end-2060\">; they''re mostly fairly open about it.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"11\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2058 citation-2059 citation-end-2059\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"12\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2058 citation-end-2058\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"13\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-149\" data-path-to-node=\"8\"><span class=\"citation-2055 citation-2056 citation-2057 citation-end-2057\">If you''re interested in volunteering for a particular job, you c<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"14\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2055 citation-2056 citation-end-2056\">an email your host to arrange the dates and establish things like accommodation and hours of work. It''s all fairly infor<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"15\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2055 citation-end-2055\">mal; there are no legal documents or anything like that. But you do b<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"16\"><!----></sup></span>oth <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"257\">(Q14) need to have some sort of written record of what''s been agreed</strong></span> before you actually arrive.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-150\" data-path-to-node=\"9\">What about problems? Well, there are too many members for the organization to be able to investigate them all, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">(Q15) <span class=\"citation-2054\">there''s an online message board where members can post details of any difficulties they''ve had</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2054 citation-end-2054\">, things like unsatisfactory accommodation or volunteers who haven''t done the work agreed, and this works very well.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"17\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">STEVEN''S PLACEMENTS (Questions 16–20)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Presenter:</strong> I know you''ve personally had lots of extra hands.com placements Steven. Tell us about them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Steven:</strong> Well, my first placement was in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">Portugal</strong></span>, where I helped a local guy with a guidebook he''d written in English. I read what he''d written and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">(Q16) corrected the English and made some suggestions for improving it (F - Editor)</strong></span>. I was very pleased with it when I finished and I learned lots about the country.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">The next placement was on the other side of the world, in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">Australia</strong></span>. I was on a farm in the middle of nowhere and since I''m pretty good in the kitchen, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">(Q17) they had me fixing meals for 30 sheep shearers (A - Cook)</strong></span>. I stayed two months and it was a lot of fun, but I can tell you I was glad to get back home to California and just lie on a beach and relax.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-151\" data-path-to-node=\"15\">Okay, then after a well-deserved rest, I did a job in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">South Korea</strong></span> for a small company that wanted an English speaker to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">(Q18) show visiting Americans around (D - Tour guide)</strong></span>. I <span class=\"citation-2052 citation-2053 citation-end-2053\">gave me some books to read and I learned as I worked. I loved it and I developed a real taste for Korean food.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"18\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2052 citation-end-2052\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"19\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-152\" data-path-to-node=\"16\"><span class=\"citation-2050 citation-2051\">My most difficult job was for an older lady in the </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"51\"><span class=\"citation-2050 citation-2051\">USA</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2050 citation-2051 citation-end-2051\">. She had a gigantic house and grounds but she couldn''t maintain them all herself. So I worked<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"20\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2050 citation-end-2050\"> for he<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"21\"><!----></sup></span>r <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">(Q19) digging and planting flowers and stuff around her swimming pool (B - Gardener)</strong></span>, and she grew tons of vegetables too. She was nice but she fed me hot dogs morning, noon and night!</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">Now my most recent placement was last summer in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">Italy</strong></span>. I helped a family <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">(Q20) add a room under their house (C - Construction worker)</strong></span>. I didn''t speak Italian or know the first thing about building, but the husband had an English-Italian phrasebook and together with sign language showed me exactly what to do. And the wife''s cooking was out of this world!</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d5a9738e-4f5b-4313-a8a8-2dbca8c50846', '8f3ec8e0-7acb-415d-93f9-9047eeb6fb48', 'radio', 'Questions 1-7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information. <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information. <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon was famous for his work before he designed the Opera House."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon’s design was favoured by the four judges of the competition from the beginning."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon’s knowledge of boats gave him the idea for parts of the Opera House."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon was impressed by the opera houses he had seen in Mexico."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon changed his designs in the 1960s after construction began."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Seidler defended Utzon’s role as architect."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon went back to Australia in 1973 for the opening of the Opera House."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong class=\"\">1. Utzon was famous for his work before he designed the Opera House.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 2) Cuộc thi thiết kế đã được </span><strong class=\"\">Jørn Utzon, một kiến trúc sư tương đối ít được biết đến</strong><span class=\"\"> (</span><em class=\"\">“a relatively little-known architect from Denmark”</em><span class=\"\">) thắng cuộc.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Utzon không nổi tiếng trước khi giành chiến thắng cuộc thi thiết kế.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">2. Utzon’s design was favoured by the four judges of the competition from the beginning.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 2) Giám khảo Eero Saarinen </span><strong class=\"\">đến sau</strong><span class=\"\"> khi ba giám khảo khác đã bắt đầu đánh giá các bài dự thi.</span><span class=\"\"> Ông </span><strong class=\"\">xem qua các bài bị loại</strong><span class=\"\"> (</span><em class=\"\">“looked through their rejected entries”</em><span class=\"\">) và dừng lại ở thiết kế của Utzon,</span><span class=\"\"> tuyên bố nó xuất sắc.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Thiết kế của Utzon ban đầu đã bị các giám khảo khác từ chối (</span><em class=\"\">rejected</em><span class=\"\">).</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">3. Utzon’s knowledge of boats gave him the idea for parts of the Opera House.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 3) “He used his maritime background to study naval charts of Sydney Harbour.</span><span class=\"\"> His early exposure to </span><strong class=\"\">shipbuilding provided the inspiration for the design of the roof</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> which is a series of curved ‘shells’ that look like the sails of a sailing ship…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Kinh nghiệm về hàng hải và đóng tàu (</span><em class=\"\">maritime background / shipbuilding</em><span class=\"\">) đã cung cấp cảm hứng cho thiết kế mái nhà.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">4. Utzon was impressed by the opera houses he had seen in Mexico.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 3) “From his travels to Mexico,</span> <strong class=\"\">he had the idea of placing his building on a wide horizontal platform</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Việc ông có ý tưởng về nền tảng rộng từ chuyến đi Mexico không có nghĩa là ông ấn tượng với các nhà hát opera ở đó.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">5. Utzon changed his designs in the 1960s after construction began.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 4) “Construction of the platform began in 1959,</span><span class=\"\"> and throughout the early 1960s </span><strong class=\"\">Utzon amended his original designs</strong><span class=\"\"> in order to develop a way to build the large ‘shells’ that cover the two main halls.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Ông đã sửa đổi thiết kế ban đầu (</span><em class=\"\">amended his original designs</em><span class=\"\">) trong những năm đầu thập niên 1960,</span><span class=\"\"> sau khi xây dựng bắt đầu vào năm 1959.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">6. Seidler defended Utzon’s role as architect.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 5) “Following his resignation,</span><span class=\"\"> there were protests through the streets led by </span><strong class=\"\">prominent architect Harry Seidler and others, demanding that Utzon be reinstated as architect</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Seidler đã dẫn đầu các cuộc biểu tình yêu cầu khôi phục vai trò kiến trúc sư trưởng cho Utzon.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">7. Utzon went back to Australia in 1973 for the opening of the Opera House.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 5) Utzon </span><strong class=\"\">“left Australia in 1966. He never returned”</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\"> Mặc dù Nhà hát Opera hoàn thành năm 1973,</span><span class=\"\"> ông chưa bao giờ quay lại.</span></li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('11a94042-837d-496a-a903-1341832c5c3e', '7ff11e44-f44a-4cef-a7fa-1b8af337f088', 'radio', 'Questions 40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A argue that Neanderthal homes were bigger than originally thought."}, {"content": "B explain why Neanderthal people migrated to Western Europe."}, {"content": "C discuss what is known about Neanderthal settlements."}, {"content": "D track the progress of early Neanderthal development"}], "question": "The purpose of the writer of this article is to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>40. The purpose of the writer of this article is to</p>\n<p>Đáp án: C. discuss what is known about Neanderthal settlements.<br />\nGiải thích: Toàn bộ bài đọc liệt kê và phân tích các bằng chứng khảo cổ về nơi ở, cấu trúc và cách sống (settlements) của người Neanderthal ở các khu vực khác nhau.</p>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('17628e05-a8f4-4b74-af81-69cf4c7b45ab', '532795f4-2eb1-4c7d-a22c-3c4328b927cb', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Washing Machine Warranty</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Personal details</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Name Judie Smith</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Reference number: {CWX576884}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Time of purchase {9|nine moth}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Current address 120 {Middle Street} , Oxford</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Postcode: {Go194KE} .</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Problems</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The floor was wet because of the {Water} .</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The washing machine was out of control and the woman {Switched off} immediately</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The floor is made of {wood} .</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Arrangement for the repair work</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Ask a {Client engineer} to repair the washing machine</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The repairman is available {next Tuesday}. </p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The woman''s house is oppsite the {Post Office} .</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8bcca6bb-8f59-4c81-998c-38304e78cb7d', '1309e07e-3d9f-487e-a665-b3c72c540cc1', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23-24', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, A–E.</p>
<p>23 – 24 Which <strong>TWO </strong>comparisons between employees who often procrastinate and those who do not are mentioned in the text?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', '[{"correct": null, "options": [{"content": null}], "question": null}]', '[{"option": "A. Their salaries are lower.", "correct": true}, {"option": "B. The quality of their work is inferior.", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. They don’t keep their jobs for as long.", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. They don’t enjoy their working lives as much.", "correct": false}, {"option": "E. They have poorer relationships with colleagues.", "correct": false}]', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>23–24. A, C<br />(Đoạn D: nói về việc trì hoãn làm giảm thu nhập và sự ổn định công việc, nhưng không đề cập đến chất lượng công việc (B) hay sự hài lòng (D), cũng không nói họ giữ việc lâu hay không (C).)<br />→ Hai so sánh không được nhắc đến trong bài là A (lương thấp hơn) và C (không giữ việc lâu).</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7b335be1-e541-4a0c-a331-927539af959e', '1ed10280-ddd8-4e0c-b4cd-41c6f5b7807f', 'fillup', 'Questions 22–26', '<p>Complete the summary.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="1288" data-end="1377"><strong data-start="1292" data-end="1377">Family-friendly practices at Plastic Solutions and the Margaret Mills Corporation</strong></p>
<p data-start="1379" data-end="1786">At Plastic Solutions, a bi-weekly update is issued to workers at the same time as their pay. This includes a section dealing with problems such as {gossip} in communal areas of the workplace. The CEO also arranges a regular {seminar} for selected employees for workplace skills which are in great demand. Finally, employees’ families are invited to company open days, when they are allowed to try out the {machines}.</p>
<p data-start="1788" data-end="2122" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">The Margaret Mills Corporation allows employees a degree of flexibility with their children, who can be brought to the office once {school} has finished. Mills likes to reward employees for company performance with a party or even a {trip} for families. There is considerable evidence that these practices are having the desired effect.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. …dealing with problems such as {gossip} in communal areas…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “This addresses issues like <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">gossip</strong>, which employees sometimes indulge in around the water cooler…” (Đoạn B)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. The CEO also arranges a regular {seminar} for selected employees…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “His employees line up to attend his monthly invitation-only Business Pragmatics <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">seminar</strong>…” (Đoạn B)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. …they are allowed to try out the {machines}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…kids can experiment with the company’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">machines</strong> that manufacture their products…” (Đoạn B)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Experiment with” tương ứng với “try out”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. …who can be brought to the office once {school} has finished.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…allows workers to have their children dropped off when <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">school</strong> is over…” (Đoạn C)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. …reward employees for company performance with a party or even a {trip} for families.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…the company took all employees and their families on a 2-day <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">trip</strong> to Montreal, Canada.” (Đoạn C)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2c36a40e-2ed9-4ca7-bbbc-fcef6f28dce8', '3a0eba5c-f8f4-47b5-a9c8-839762c5bb35', 'radio', 'Questions 27 – 32', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C or D.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A He has lived among the Pirahã since 1977."}, {"content": "B It took him seven years to learn the Pirahã language."}, {"content": "C No one would publish his research for three decades."}, {"content": "D Studying the Pirahã language is the focus of his work."}], "question": "What are we told about Daniel Everett in the first paragraph?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A Humans are the only species to be linguistically creative."}, {"content": "B Humans, bees, birds and whales share a characteristic."}, {"content": "C Human language is not fully understood by scientists."}, {"content": "D Humans are the only species to use syntax."}], "question": "Which of the following is the best summary of the second paragraph?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A to criticise the general approach of linguistics"}, {"content": "B to compare two features of the Pirahã language"}, {"content": "C to explain why the Pirahã language is difficult to learn"}, {"content": "D to exemplify an unusual feature of the Pirahã language"}], "question": "Why does the writer refer to subordinate clauses?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A He thought that numbers were common to all human languages."}, {"content": "B His theory might be supported by Everett’s research."}, {"content": "C His research enabled him to find a new life among the Pirahã."}, {"content": "D He predicted that people like the Pirahã would never be found."}], "question": "What point does the writer make about the work of Whorf?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A suggest that the Pirahã be taught to count in English."}, {"content": "B show how tribal peoples learn a foreign language."}, {"content": "C compare counting in English and Portuguese."}, {"content": "D illustrate the uniqueness of the Pirahã."}], "question": "The writer refers to the Warlpiri people in order to"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A Pirahã students have not graduated from universities."}, {"content": "B He does not want people to criticise their intelligence."}, {"content": "C Their isolation makes it difficult to evaluate their intelligence."}, {"content": "D He believes their language is more complex than their neighbours’."}], "question": "What is Everett’s point about the Pirahã’s intellectual capacities?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>27. What are we told about Daniel Everett in the first paragraph?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: D. Studying the Pirahã language is the focus of his work.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “…Daniel Everett has spent a total of seven years living with the Pirahã and has <strong>committed his career to studying their puzzling speech</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “committed his career” (cống hiến sự nghiệp) cho thấy việc nghiên cứu ngôn ngữ Pirahã là trọng tâm công việc của ông.\n<ul>\n<li><em>(Loại trừ: A sai, ông sống tổng cộng 7 năm, không phải “since 1977”. B, C sai vì không có thông tin về thời gian học ngôn ngữ hay việc không ai chịu xuất bản.</em>)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>28. Which of the following is the best summary of the second paragraph?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A. Humans are the only species to be linguistically creative.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “…human language is unique, if only for the reason that it enables humans to <strong>piece together never-before-constructed thoughts, and be infinitely imaginative</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn nhấn mạnh tính <strong>duy nhất</strong> (unique) của ngôn ngữ con người nằm ở khả năng sáng tạo vô hạn (infinitely imaginative) và tạo ra các ý tưởng chưa từng có.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>29. Why does the writer refer to subordinate clauses?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: D. to exemplify an unusual feature of the Pirahã language.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “Most of all, it may be unique for <strong>not employing subordinate clauses</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ngay sau câu này, tác giả đưa ra ví dụ so sánh (“Instead of saying… the Pirahã say…”) để minh họa cho một đặc điểm <strong>bất thường/độc đáo</strong> (unusual feature) của ngôn ngữ Pirahã.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>30. What point does the writer make about the work of Whorf?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: B. His theory might be supported by Everett’s research.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “Everett’s findings among the Pirahã have <strong>brought new life to a controversial theory by the linguist Benjamin Whorf</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Kết quả của Everett đã làm sống lại lý thuyết của Whorf (rằng con người chỉ có thể xây dựng những suy nghĩ mà họ có từ ngữ tương ứng), ngụ ý nghiên cứu của Everett <strong>ủng hộ</strong> (supported) lý thuyết đó.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>31. The writer refers to the Warlpiri people in order to</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: D. illustrate the uniqueness of the Pirahã.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “However, the Warlpiri people had <strong>no difficulty counting</strong> farther than three in a foreign language… but when Everett attempted to teach the Pirahã… <strong>not a single person could count to 10</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc so sánh với người Warlpiri (những người có thể học đếm) nhằm mục đích làm nổi bật sự khác biệt và <strong>tính độc đáo</strong> (uniqueness) của người Pirahã khi họ hoàn toàn không thể học đếm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>32. What is Everett’s point about the Pirahã’s intellectual capacities?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: B. He does not want people to criticise their intelligence.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “<strong>Everett is at pains to point out that the Pirahã are not unintelligent</strong>… for their thinking is not any slower than that of the average university student.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “At pains to point out” (rất cố gắng để chỉ ra) cho thấy ông muốn <strong>ngăn chặn</strong> (does not want) việc mọi người nghĩ rằng người Pirahã là kém thông minh.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e0c5fcee-ab3f-4adb-8ee4-64a5a9d97444', '3a0eba5c-f8f4-47b5-a9c8-839762c5bb35', 'matching', 'Questions 33 – 36', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words, A–I, below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, A–I, in boxes 33-36</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Everett''s explanation</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Everett believes that a group''s language is a product of their {E culture} and thus language is infinitely varied. During the time he spent living among them, he observed that the Pirahã only place value on the {A present} and have no {F grammar} to describe completed events. Similarly, the types of names they use reflect the fact that they do not celebrate {H individuality}.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A present"}, {"optionText": "B past"}, {"optionText": "C time"}, {"optionText": "D future"}, {"optionText": "E culture"}, {"optionText": "F grammar"}, {"optionText": "G art"}, {"optionText": "H individuality"}, {"optionText": "I children"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>33. Everett believes that a group’s language is a product of their <strong>culture</strong>…</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: E. culture</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “Language, he believes, is created by a people’s way of life, their <strong>belief system and values</strong>.” (Tín ngưỡng và giá trị sống tạo nên văn hóa.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>34. …he observed that the Pirahã only place value on the <strong>present</strong>…</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A. present</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “…the central tenet of the Pirahã culture is to live in the <strong>here and now</strong>.” (“Here and now” đồng nghĩa với hiện tại – <strong>present</strong>.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>35. …and have no <strong>grammar</strong> to describe completed events.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: F. grammar</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “In consequence, the language has <strong>no means to conjugate verbs</strong> in order to describe ‘yesterday’ or ‘last week’…” (Việc không có phương tiện để chia động từ là thiếu hụt về mặt ngữ pháp – <strong>grammar</strong>.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>36. Similarly, the types of names they use reflect the fact that they do not celebrate <strong>individuality</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: H. individuality</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “Standing out or being different is <strong>not encouraged</strong> by the Pirahã, and this is reflected in their perhaps colourless choice of names.” (Việc không khuyến khích “standing out or being different” đồng nghĩa với không đề cao <strong>tính cá nhân</strong> – individuality.)</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8fbceecc-1177-489d-9dd4-766c44fc9834', '3a0eba5c-f8f4-47b5-a9c8-839762c5bb35', 'radio', 'Questions 37 – 40 ', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT</strong> <strong>GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": " YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Everett was surprised by the way his research was greeted."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Chomsky has been critical of Everett''s research methodology."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "If ''recursion'' as a universal concept is disproved, Chomsky''s ideas about language would be wrong."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Pirahã will benefit from their new-found status among academics."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>37. Everett was surprised by the way his research was greeted.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NO</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “<strong>Everett anticipated that these findings would be controversial and the reaction came as expected</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ông đã lường trước (anticipated) sự tranh cãi và phản ứng diễn ra <strong>đúng như dự đoán</strong> (came as expected), tức là ông không hề ngạc nhiên.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>38. Chomsky has been critical of Everett’s research methodology.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8, 9) Văn bản chỉ nói rằng nghiên cứu của Everett làm lung lay các lý thuyết của Chomsky và các đồng nghiệp của Chomsky sẽ đến Brazil kiểm tra.</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> <strong>Không có thông tin</strong> nào cho biết đích thân Chomsky đã chỉ trích phương pháp nghiên cứu (methodology) của Everett.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>39. If ‘recursion’ as a universal concept is disproved, Chomsky’s ideas about language would be wrong.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: YES</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “But if the Pirahã do not form subordinate clauses, then recursion cannot explain the uniqueness of human language, and <strong>this would negate Chomsky’s theories</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản khẳng định rằng nếu người Pirahã không dùng mệnh đề phụ (liên quan đến recursion), thì điều này sẽ <strong>phủ nhận</strong> (negate) lý thuyết của Chomsky.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>40. The Pirahã will benefit from their new-found status among academics.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NO</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) “<strong>My concern is that soon the Pirahã will simply become one more scientific oddity with every aspect of their lives being exploited and analysed</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả bày tỏ <strong>lo ngại</strong> (My concern is that) rằng bộ tộc sẽ bị khai thác (exploited) và phân tích, ngụ ý rằng họ <strong>không được hưởng lợi</strong> (will not benefit).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('89796da5-98b1-401d-8f10-04d5b8b6149c', '4362ff2e-6573-47e1-9c73-1b10ec6a275a', 'radio', 'Questions 27 – 30', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="27">A, B, C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="38">D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "fear and stress are different feelings."}, {"option_text": "most humans develop strategies for dealing with fear."}, {"option_text": "business situations cause more fear than others."}, {"option_text": "some people never experience fear."}], "question": " In the first paragraph, the writer points out that"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "they react more quickly to fear than humans."}, {"option_text": "they are more influenced by fear than humans."}, {"option_text": "their mental growth resembles that of humans."}, {"option_text": "their brains work more slowly than those of humans."}], "question": "When discussing the use of rhesus monkeys as experimental subjects, the writer notes that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "the identification of expressions of anxiety in monkeys"}, {"option_text": "the identification of situations that arouse stress in monkeys"}, {"option_text": "an analysis of brain development in monkeys"}, {"option_text": "the study of reactions to fear in monkeys of different ages"}], "question": "Which of the following did Kalin and Shelton outline as the second stage in their research project?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "reflect common experiences for infant humans and monkeys."}, {"option_text": "highlight the similarities between monkey and human infant care."}, {"option_text": "were predicted to cause monkeys more distress than human infants."}, {"option_text": "were graded in terms of their potential effect on young monkeys."}], "question": "In the fourth paragraph, the writer notes that the three related situations"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. In the first paragraph, the writer points out that — {B} most humans develop strategies for dealing with fear.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Over the years, the majority of people acquire a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">range of skills for coping with frightening situations</strong>.” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Acquire a range of skills for coping with” tương ứng với “develop strategies for dealing with”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. When discussing the use of rhesus monkeys… — {C} their mental growth resembles that of humans.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “These animals undergo many of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">same physiological and psychological developmental stages</strong> that humans do…” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Psychological developmental stages” chính là sự phát triển về tâm thần/trí tuệ (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">mental growth</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. Which of the following did Kalin and Shelton outline as the second stage…? — {D} the study of reactions to fear in monkeys of different ages.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…they could then proceed to <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">determine the age</strong> at which monkeys begin to match defensive behaviors selectively to specific cues.” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bước thứ hai là xác định độ tuổi mà khỉ bắt đầu có phản ứng phòng vệ có chọn lọc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. In the fourth paragraph, the writer notes that the three related situations — {A} reflect common experiences for infant humans and monkeys.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “These positions are <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">no more frightening than those that primates encounter frequently in the wild, or those that human infants meet</strong> whenever they are left at a day-care centre.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả so sánh 3 tình huống thí nghiệm với những trải nghiệm đời thường của khỉ ngoài tự nhiên và trẻ em ở nhà trẻ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('892d2d33-ae81-4f6c-955f-2e36bdb08adc', 'a73c6549-8c8e-4355-9425-19058dc8673b', 'checkbox', 'Questions 13 and 14', '', '<p data-path-to-node="20">Choose <strong data-path-to-node="20" data-index-in-node="7">TWO</strong> letters, <strong data-path-to-node="20" data-index-in-node="20">A–E</strong>.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="21">Which <strong data-path-to-node="21" data-index-in-node="6">TWO</strong> tips does Liz recommend for new runners?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A   doing two runs a week"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B   running in the evening"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C   going on runs with a friend"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D   listening to music during runs"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E   running very slowly"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cddf500e-200f-42e2-b2a0-b7bc18df2452', '4362ff2e-6573-47e1-9c73-1b10ec6a275a', 'matrix', 'Questions 31 – 35', '', '<p>Look at the following responses of monkeys and the list of conditions below.</p>
<p>Match each response with the correct condition, <strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="125">A, B</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="133">C</strong>.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of options", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Aggressive facial expressions", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "prolonged stillness", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "a combination of contradictory signals", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "appeals for maternal protection", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "the production of soft sounds", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "the alone condition", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "the no-eye-contact condition", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "the stare condition", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Aggressive facial expressions — {C: The stare condition}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “The monkeys made several <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">hostile gestures</strong>: barking… and <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">staring back</strong>.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hành động nhìn chằm chằm lại và sủa là biểu cảm hung dữ/tấn công.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Prolonged stillness — {B: The no-eye-contact condition}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…the monkeys reduced their activity greatly and sometimes <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">froze for extended periods of time</strong>.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Froze” (đứng hình/đông cứng) tương ứng với “stillness”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. A combination of contradictory signals — {C: The stare condition}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Sometimes the animals <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">mixed the threatening displays with submissive ones</strong>…” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc kết hợp giữa đe dọa (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">threatening</em>) và phục tùng (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">submissive</em>) chính là các tín hiệu mâu thuẫn/trái ngược nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Appeals for maternal protection — {A: The alone condition}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…it <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">yearns to regain the closeness and security</strong> provided by nearness to the parent. These responses help to <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">draw the mother’s attention</strong>.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. The production of soft sounds — {A: The alone condition}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…emitted frequent <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">gentle “coo” calls</strong>…” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Gentle calls” tương ứng với “soft sounds”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e7424e9c-031f-4c40-9cac-68fb797524fa', '61455c9f-22c7-4239-b946-4365ee8f349a', 'matching', 'Questions 27-30', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words and phrases, A-H, below.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MEHRABIAN’S 1967 STUDY</strong></p>\r\n<p>Albert Mehrabian and his colleagues carried out an influential study comparing the {D effects} of verbal and non-verbal communication. This involved two experiments. In both experiments, subjects had to identify the {G fellings} being communicated by other people. The two main areas focused on in the first experiment were voice tones and {A facial expression} while the second focused mainly on voice tones and {E word meanings} .</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A facial expression"}, {"optionText": "B purposes"}, {"optionText": "C printed words"}, {"optionText": "D effects"}, {"optionText": "E word meanings"}, {"optionText": "F gender differences"}, {"optionText": "G fellings"}, {"optionText": "H characteristics"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong>27. D</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;The findings of a study on verbal and non-verbal messages in communication&#8230; have been quoted so frequently&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu so sánh <strong>tác động</strong> (<strong>effects</strong>) của các kênh giao tiếp khác nhau lên thông điệp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>28. G</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;&#8230;were asked to <strong>guess the emotions</strong> in the recorded voice and the photos.&#8221; và &#8220;&#8230;the subjects had to <strong>guess the speaker&#8217;s emotions</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cả hai thí nghiệm đều yêu cầu đối tượng nhận biết <strong>cảm xúc</strong> (<strong>emotions</strong> / <strong>feelings</strong>) được truyền đạt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong>29. A</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;&#8230;three tones of voice&#8230; The subjects were then shown <strong>photos of female faces</strong> expressing the same three emotions&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thí nghiệm đầu tiên so sánh giọng điệu (<strong>voice tones</strong>) và biểu cảm khuôn mặt (<strong>facial expressions</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong>30. E</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;&#8230;listened to nine recorded words spoken in different tones of voice. Three words had positive <strong>meanings</strong> (e.g. <em>honey</em>)&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thí nghiệm thứ hai so sánh giọng điệu và <strong>ý nghĩa từ ngữ</strong> (<strong>word meanings</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f11583b7-7bc6-4419-9d19-19a670ca3e09', 'a39a2927-fa38-49de-8500-ce2b13770ce9', 'fillup', 'Question 33–36', '<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.<br />Write your answers in boxes 33–36 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>Which creatures are particularly well underwater? {mantis shrimp}</p>
<p>In addition to a computer, what technical equipment is fitted in Dr Zelenisky’s robot? {panoramic camera}</p>
<p>Where is the Cataglyphis ant found? {Sahara desert}</p>
<p>What atmospheric effect helps the Cataglyphis ant to know its direction? {polarized light}</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 33: Which creatures see particularly well underwater?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> Mantis Shrimp</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">mantis shrimp</strong> scans its aquatic world through hyperspectral eyes.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tôm tít (mantis shrimp) có thị giác cực tốt trong môi trường nước nhờ đôi mắt đa phổ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 34: In addition to a computer, what technical equipment is fitted in Dr Zelinsky’s robot?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> Panoramic camera</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…a robot can navigate its way… using a <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">panoramic camera</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngoài máy tính, robot của Dr. Zelinsky còn được trang bị camera toàn cảnh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 35: Where is the Cataglyphis ant found?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> Sahara desert</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…journeyed from Switzerland to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">Sahara desert</strong> where <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">Cataglyphis</strong>, a tiny ant… performs acts of navigational genius…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Loài kiến Cataglyphis được tìm thấy ở sa mạc Sahara.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 36: What atmospheric effect helps the Catalyphis ant to know its direction?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> Polarized light</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Cataglyphis</strong> uses <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">polarised light</strong>, caused when air molecules scatter light, to orient and steer itself.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hiện tượng ánh sáng phân cực trong khí quyển giúp loài kiến này định hướng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2278fb64-4eb3-4ac6-9f52-c17ffcab857b', 'a39a2927-fa38-49de-8500-ce2b13770ce9', 'matching', 'Question 37–40', NULL, '<p>Look at the following people and the list of robots below.</p>
<p>Match each person or people with the correct robot <strong>A–G</strong>.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. a robot that makes use of light as well as stored images for navigational purposes"}, {"optionText": "B. a robot that can contribute to environmental health"}, {"optionText": "C. a robot that can move over difficult surfaces"}, {"optionText": "D. a robot that categorises information from the environment according to its usefulness"}, {"optionText": "E. a robot that can be used to clean surfaces and collect rubbish"}, {"optionText": "F. a robot that has improved on the ability of the insect on which it is based"}, {"optionText": "G. a robot that can replace soldiers in war"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Dr Alex Zelinsky", "correctAnswer": "D. a robot that categorises information from the environment according to its usefulness", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Professor Ruediger Wehner", "correctAnswer": "A. a robot that makes use of light as well as stored images for navigational purposes", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Professor Robert Michelson", "correctAnswer": "F. a robot that has improved on the ability of the insect on which it is based", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Roger Quinn and Professor Roy Ritzmann", "correctAnswer": "C. a robot that can move over difficult surfaces", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 37: Dr Alex Zelinsky</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> D</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mô tả robot D:</strong> Một robot phân loại thông tin từ môi trường theo mức độ hữu ích.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The robot’s panoramic camera logs the surrounding area… which are then <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">sorted in its computer according to how reliable they are</strong> as navigational aids.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 38: Professor Ruediger Wehner</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> A</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mô tả robot A:</strong> Một robot sử dụng ánh sáng và hình ảnh lưu trữ để định vị.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Using the ant’s ability to steer by <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">polarised light</strong> and to <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">store and reuse landscape images</strong>, Wehner… built ‘Sahabot’…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 39: Professor Robert Michelson</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> F</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mô tả robot F:</strong> Một robot cải tiến khả năng của loài côn trùng mà nó dựa trên đó.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…he has <strong data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">gone beyond nature</strong> to devise a completely new concept… enabling it to fly slowly or hover in the thin Martain air…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Michelson không chỉ mô phỏng mà còn vượt xa tự nhiên (cải tiến) để robot có thể bay trong khí quyển mỏng của sao Hỏa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 40: Roger Quinn and Professor Roy Ritzmann</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"37\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> C</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mô tả robot C:</strong> Một robot có thể di chuyển trên các bề mặt khó khăn.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…enabling them to handle <strong data-path-to-node=\"37,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">surprisingly rugged terrain</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Robot dựa trên loài gián của họ được thiết kế để vượt qua các địa hình hiểm trở (rugged terrain).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8cdd62b2-8c07-4e7b-86ad-d435c803ea9c', '4362ff2e-6573-47e1-9c73-1b10ec6a275a', 'fillup', 'Questions 36 – 40', '<p>Choose<strong> NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS AND / OR A NUMBER </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Once they had identified three types of defensive behaviour, Kalin and Shelton grouped the monkeys according to their {age}, in order to discover precisely when they were able to respond appropriately to different fear-related cues. They videotaped their results and found that monkeys as young as {two weeks old}<span class="citation-623"> reacted to the cues but in a haphazard fashion. The researchers noted that they seemed to be unaware of the {human beings}</span><span class="citation-623"> who were around them. Despite demonstrating {good motor control}</span><span class="citation-623 citation-end-623">, the monkeys in the middle groups fai</span>led to react in ways corresponding to the experimental situation. The oldest group, however, reacted in the same way as {mature monkeys} and the researchers concluded that monkeys are capable of selective responding between nine and 12 weeks old.</p>', '', 'short_answer', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. …grouped the monkeys according to their {age}…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…they examined four groups of infant monkeys <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">ranging in age</strong> up to 12 weeks old.” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. …monkeys as young as {two weeks old} reacted to the cues…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “They found that the infants in the youngest group (<strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">no more than two weeks old</strong>) engaged in defensive behaviours…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. …they seemed to be unaware of the {human beings} who were around them.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…as if they had not noticed the <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">human beings</strong> that were present.” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Had not noticed” tương ứng với “unaware of”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Despite demonstrating {good motor control}…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Babies in the two intermediate-age groups had <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">good motor control</strong>…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. …reacted in the same way as {mature monkeys}…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"34\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…their reactions were both appropriate and identical to those of <strong data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">mature monkeys</strong>.” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0432bc28-15d2-48bb-9744-463e429d0ac3', '57ece189-00b1-4012-b0fd-d77735bc7f26', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23–24', '', '<p data-start="411" data-end="439">Choose <strong data-start="418" data-end="438">TWO letters, A–E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="441" data-end="545">Which <strong data-start="447" data-end="454">TWO</strong> health risks associated with loneliness do the students agree are based on solid evidence?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A a weakened immune system"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B dementia"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C cancer"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D obesity"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E cardiovascular disease"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('125b009f-847e-4d2a-9e05-9157e64f1363', '61455c9f-22c7-4239-b946-4365ee8f349a', 'radio', 'Questions 36-40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A It makes the claims more attractive."}, {"content": "B It is the strongest point of the study."}, {"content": "C It will appeal to superstitious people"}, {"content": "D It allows comparison between languages."}], "question": "What does the writer say about the ‘numerical precision’ of Mehrabian’s study?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A It is unlikely to maintain its present status"}, {"content": "B It is leading to an undervaluing of language"}, {"content": "C It should be applied in a more practical way"}, {"content": "D It may help understanding of non-verbal messages"}], "question": " What does the writer say about the popularity of the 7-38-55 formula?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A Language could be learned more efficiently than it is"}, {"content": "B More research is needed into attitudes to communication"}, {"content": "C More time should be spent looking at tone and body language"}, {"content": "D Language must be important since we make an effort to acquire it"}], "question": "What point is Bradley making about language learning?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A They are relevant to only one area of communication."}, {"content": "B It is only in maths that 100% of communication is verbal."}, {"content": "C Feelings are more difficult to communicate than numerical facts."}, {"content": "D Non-verbal communication is the main part of the message."}], "question": "What does Mehrabian himself say about his findings?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A to justify the strong points of Mehrabian’s study"}, {"content": "B to outline other research on non-verbal behaviour"}, {"content": "C to present varying interpretations of Mehrabian’s study"}, {"content": "D to show that textbooks tend to ignore non-verbal behaviour"}], "question": " What is the writer’s purpose in the paragraph beginning ‘To be fair …’?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>36. What does the writer say about the ‘numerical precision’ of Mehrabian’s study?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: A. It makes the claims more attractive.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;Clearly, one <strong>appealing aspect</strong> of the Mehrabian study is its <strong>numerical precision</strong>&#8230; Communication is a complex phenomenon, but it seems less so when we can rely on these three magical numbers.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tính chính xác bằng số (numerical precision) làm cho nghiên cứu trở nên <strong>hấp dẫn</strong> (<strong>appealing</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>37. What does the writer say about the popularity of the 7-38-55 formula?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: B. It is leading to an undervaluing of language.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;&#8230;the continued references to this research sustain it, encouraging people to believe in the overwhelming importance of the non-verbal message compared with the verbal one. <strong>Yet we know that even one ill-chosen word to a colleague or friend can make or break a communicative effort</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công thức này khuyến khích người ta đề cao phi ngôn ngữ và <strong>đánh giá thấp</strong> (<strong>undervaluing</strong>) vai trò của ngôn ngữ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>38. What point is Bradley making about language learning?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: D. Language must be important since we make an effort to acquire it.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) Bradley observes, <strong>‘If we could communicate 93% of information and attitudes with vocal and facial cues, it would be wasteful to spend time learning a language.’</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bradley lập luận rằng việc con người nỗ lực học ngôn ngữ cho thấy ngôn ngữ phải có vai trò quan trọng, nếu không thì việc học sẽ là lãng phí.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>39. What does Mehrabian himself say about his findings?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: A. They are relevant to only one area of communication.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) &#8220;<strong>Please remember that alt my findings … dealt with communications of feelings and attitudes</strong> … it is absurd to imply or suggest that the verbal portion of all communication constitutes only 7% of the message&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Mehrabian tự giới hạn phạm vi áp dụng của nghiên cứu chỉ trong việc truyền đạt cảm xúc và thái độ (<strong>feelings and attitudes</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>40. What is the writer’s purpose in the paragraph beginning ‘To be fair …’?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: C. to present varying interpretations of Mehrabian’s study</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) &#8220;To be fair, <strong>many textbook writers attempt to be faithful to the context</strong>&#8230; <strong>Others try to play down the specific percentages</strong>&#8230; <strong>Nonetheless, ether textbook authors simply use the numbers</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn mô tả <strong>các cách hiểu khác nhau</strong> (varying interpretations) về nghiên cứu của Mehrabian trong sách giáo khoa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('651e002b-960f-49a2-8013-2f86bad168bc', '3c523f98-9749-47dc-bca4-6e975a29317e', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–7', '<p data-start="116" data-end="180">Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="116" data-end="180"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Community Centre Classes</strong></span></p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 325.6px; border: 1.5px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 24.9384%;"> <col style="width: 24.9384%;"> <col style="width: 24.9384%;"> <col style="width: 24.9384%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 61.2px;">
